Class IntOrderedIterator<E>

  • java.lang.Object
    • edu.stanford.math.plex4.streams.storage_structures.IntOrderedIterator<E>
  • Type Parameters:
    E -
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.util.Iterator<E>

    public class IntOrderedIterator<E>
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.util.Iterator<E>
    This class provides iteration over the second component of each element in an Iterable collection of type IntObjectPair. It essentially ignores the first component, and only returns the second.
    Author:
    Andrew Tausz
